stateDiagram-v2

    [*] --> Parsing
    Parsing : Parsing<br/>--------<br/>parse argv<br/>read env vars<br/>read config files

    Parsing --> Validating : args parsed
    Parsing --> UsageError : malformed args<br/>(exit 64)

    Validating : Validating<br/>--------<br/>check required<br/>verify constraints<br/>resolve config layering

    Validating --> Authenticating : valid + auth needed
    Validating --> Executing : valid + no auth
    Validating --> ConfigError : missing config<br/>(exit 78)

    Authenticating : Authenticating<br/>--------<br/>read credentials<br/>(env / stdin / helper)<br/>NOT command-line args

    Authenticating --> Executing : auth ok
    Authenticating --> AuthError : auth failed<br/>(exit 77)

    Executing : Executing<br/>--------<br/>perform action<br/>tool's primary work<br/>handle SIGPIPE

    Executing --> Formatting : success
    Executing --> NetworkError : network failed<br/>(exit 71)
    Executing --> RuntimeError : action failed<br/>(exit 1)

    Formatting : Formatting<br/>--------<br/>detect TTY vs pipe<br/>human or JSON<br/>emit to stdout

    Formatting --> Success : output emitted

    Success : Success<br/>--------<br/>exit code 0
    UsageError : UsageError<br/>--------<br/>stderr: usage<br/>exit 64
    ConfigError : ConfigError<br/>--------<br/>stderr: config issue<br/>exit 78
    AuthError : AuthError<br/>--------<br/>stderr: auth failure<br/>exit 77
    NetworkError : NetworkError<br/>--------<br/>stderr: network error<br/>exit 71
    RuntimeError : RuntimeError<br/>--------<br/>stderr: action failed<br/>exit 1

    Success --> [*]
    UsageError --> [*]
    ConfigError --> [*]
    AuthError --> [*]
    NetworkError --> [*]
    RuntimeError --> [*]

    note right of Authenticating
        Credentials read from
        env / stdin / helper —
        never from command-line
        flags (leak to shell history,
        ps listings, CI logs)
    end note

    note right of Formatting
        TTY detection drives format:
        human-readable for terminals,
        structured (JSON) for pipes.
        stdout = data; stderr = status.
    end note
